The '''Institut Européen d’archéologie Sous-Marine''' (IEASM)<ref>http://www.ieasm.org/ Institut Européen d'Archéologie Sous-Marine official website</ref>(English: European Institute for [[Underwater archaeology|Underwater Archaeology]]) was founded in 1987 as a French [[non-profit organisation]] by President [[Franck Goddio]]. The organisation locates, explores, [[Excavation (archaeology)|excavates]] and restores sunken sites. IEASM calls upon scientists and specialists<ref>http://www.arch.ox.ac.uk/ocma.html/ Oxford Center for maritime Archaeology (OCMA)</ref> of different scientific field to support its research missions, study and publish<ref>http://www.oxbowbooks.com/results.cfm/q/franck%20goddio/qt/Title,Author/ST/QS/StartRow/1//Location/DBBC Oxbow Books</ref> the findings. The organisation features exhibitions allowing the general public to get access to its discoveries.

