rum, Norwich|The Forum]] || Norwich || [[Hopkins Architects|Michael Hopkins and Partners]] || "all entrance ... a huge and crude building" || ''Eye'' 1045 p. 12 |- |2002 ||Extension to [[Manchester City Art Gallery|City Art Gallery]] || Manchester || [[Hopkins Architects|Michael Hopkins and Partners]] || "the splendid and really ''beautiful'' interiors of the original building .. have been gratuitously spoiled" || ''Eye'' 1070 p. 12 |- |2003 ||Juxon House, [[Paternoster Square]] || London || [[William Whitfield (architect)|William Whitfield]] || "an overdone embarrassing compromise, a dog's dinner" || ''Eye'' 1097 p. 15 |- |2004 ||[[Scottish Parliament Building]]<ref group="n">This building uniquely won the [[Stirling Prize]] for excellence in architecture in the same year.</ref> || Edinburgh || [[Enric Miralles]] || "confused and confusing mish-mash of upturned boats and leaflike forms" || ''Eye'' 1122 p. 12 |- |2005 ||[[Monument to the Women of World War II]] || London || [[John W. Mills]] || "crude and inept ... from a distance, the memorial becomes an incoherent dark lump, formless and inelegant" || ''Eye'' 1149 p. 14 |- |2006 ||Palestra, [[Blackfriars Road]] || London || [[Will Alsop|SMC Alsop]] || "a giant gimmick that is also plain ugly" || ''Eye'' 1174 p. 14 |- |2007 ||''[[St Pancras railway station#Public art|The Meeting Place]]'' statue, St Pancras station || London || [[Paul Day (sculptor)|Paul Day]] || "this tasteless creation" || ''Eye'' 1200 p. 14 |- |2008 ||[[The Public, West Bromwich|The Public]] || West Bromwich || [[Will Alsop]] || "a big box ... with no obvious entrances" || ''Eye'' 1226 p. 12 |- |2009 ||[[One Hyde Park]]<ref group="n" name="2011 carbuncle">Shortlisted for [[Building Design]] magazine's [[Carbuncle Cup]] in 2011.</ref> || London || [[Rogers Stirk Harbour + Partners]] || "an overweening (half-empty) ... masterpiece" || ''Eye'' 1252 p. 15 |- |2010 ||[[One New Change]] || London || [[Jean Nouvel]] || "on this crucial, prominent site,