{{nihongo|'''''Rilu Rilu Fairilu'''''|リルリルフェアリル|Riru Riru Feariru|lead=yes}} is a character [[Media franchise|franchise]] created in collaboration by [[Sanrio]] and [[Sega Sammy Holdings]], illustrated by character designer [[Ai Setani]] (''[[:ja:KIRIMIちゃん.|KIRIMI-chan]]'').<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www7.atwiki.jp/anime_wiki/pages/22909.html|title=リルリルフェアリル～魔法の鏡～|publisher=アニメ@wiki|accessdate=2017-07-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet |author=アニメ「リルリルフェアリル」公式 |user= rilurilu_anime|number= 843040737667178496|date= 18 Mar 2017 |title= Tweet introducing a Rilu Rilu Fairilu designer sign event which features KIRIMI-chan's designer|access-date= 2017-07-14}}</ref> It is the second Sanrio franchise that was handled by two companies, the first being [[Jewelpet]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-11/sanrio-sega-toys-collaborate-on-rilu-rilu-fairilu-tv-anime/.96387|title=Sanrio, Sega Toys Collaborate on Rilu Rilu Fairilu TV Anime|publisher=}}</ref> The franchise was officially launched in December 2015.<ref>http://www.segatoys.co.jp/company/press_release/pdf/20151211.pdf</ref><ref>http://www.sanrio.co.jp/news/rf-rilurilufairilu-debut-20151211/</ref>

An anime adaptation produced by [[Studio DEEN]], titled "'''Rilu Rilu Fairilu ~Yousei no Door~'''", aired on all [[TX Network|TXN]] stations in Japan from February 6, 2016 to March 25, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000163.000001909.html|title=セガトイズとサンリオの共同開発キャラクター第2弾のテレビアニメ『リルリルフェアリル〜妖精のドア〜』2016年2月よりテレビ東京他にて放送スタート！|publisher=}}</ref> A second season titled "'''Rilu Rilu Fairilu ~Maho no Kagami~'''" began airing from April 7, 2017 to March 30, 2018.<ref name="Anime News Network">{{Cite news
|date=2017-03-02|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-03-02/rilu-rilu-fairilu-tv-anime-gets-2nd-season-starting-on-april-7/.112892|title=Rilu Rilu Fairilu TV Anime Gets 2nd Season Starting on April 7|publisher=|work=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=2017-06-28}}</ref> A 3rd season titled "'''Oshiete Mahou no Pendulum ~Rilu Rilu Fairilu~'''" began its airing on July 7, 2018.<ref name="thirdseason">{{Cite news
|date=2018-05-31|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-05-31/rilu-rilu-fairilu-3rd-season-cast-title-july-premiere-revealed/.132242|title=Rilu Rilu Fairilu 3rd Season's Cast, Title, July Premiere Revealed|publisher=|work=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=2018-05-31}}</ref>

==Story==
<!--This is appliable for the first two seasons of the anime series, but starting from season 3 the story has changed-->
In a strange magical world of Little Fairilu live the Fairilus: small magical fairies representing flowers, insects and other entities who all born from the Fairilu Seed. Each Fairilu is born with its own key, the Fairilu Key, that can open magical doors, casting magic spells. If the Fairilu finds the right door, it can finally mature into a full-fledged fairy. The doors also link to the human world. Fairilus must study and go to school to learn about the world in which they live, while meeting new friends.

===1st & 2nd Series===
The anime series focuses on Lip, a newly-born Flower Fairilu, and her friends in Little Fairlu. The series follows Lip's overall life in Little Fairilu while making new friends and learning from everything around her, growing up day after day. It also tells about the Fairilu friends' adventures in the human world, where they can meet their human partners who support their dreams and are willing to help each other fulfill them.

===3rd Series===
The anime tells about a human girl called Arisu Hanazono, who by chance discovered a magical pendulum and book, summoning Fairilus. She is a girl with many worries, but by meeting the friendly Fairilus and traveling into their homeworld, Little Fairilu, she gets a chance to solve her problems and change herself.

